From: Xavier Roche <xavier.roche@algolia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] malloc: release physical pages from large interior free chunks

Since glibc 2.26 (tcache introduction), free() no longer returns
physical memory for interior heap chunks. tcache intercepts freed
chunks before consolidation, preventing the merge-and-trim path that
previously returned memory via systrim/heap_trim.

Extend _int_free_maybe_trim to call madvise(MADV_DONTNEED) on the
page-aligned interior of consolidated free chunks that already exceed
ATTEMPT_TRIMMING_THRESHOLD (64 KB). This code path already calls
systrim and heap_trim (both syscalls), so one additional madvise is
not a new class of overhead.

The signature of _int_free_maybe_trim gains a chunk pointer parameter
so it can compute the madvise region. The only call site already has
the pointer in scope.

AI disclosure: AI tools (Claude) were used during research, analysis,
and patch drafting. The author reviewed and tested everything. The
patch logic reuses the existing mtrim() page-alignment pattern.

Signed-off-by: Xavier Roche <xavier.roche@algolia.com>
---
 malloc/malloc.c | 20 ++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/malloc/malloc.c b/malloc/malloc.c
index 6455a1b0e0..XXXX 100644
--- a/malloc/malloc.c
+++ b/malloc/malloc.c
@@ -4434,8 +4434,9 @@ _int_free_create_chunk (...)
 /* If the total unused topmost memory exceeds trim threshold, ask malloc_trim
    to reduce top.  */
 static void
-_int_free_maybe_trim (mstate av, INTERNAL_SIZE_T size)
+_int_free_maybe_trim (mstate av, mchunkptr p, INTERNAL_SIZE_T size)
 {
+
   /* We don't want to trim on each free.  As a compromise, trimming is attempted
      if ATTEMPT_TRIMMING_THRESHOLD is reached.  */
   if (size >= ATTEMPT_TRIMMING_THRESHOLD)
@@ -4443,6 +4444,21 @@ _int_free_maybe_trim (mstate av, INTERNAL_SIZE_T size)
+      /* Release physical pages from the interior of this free chunk.
+	 Without this, interior chunks retain their physical pages
+	 indefinitely because top-chunk trimming only operates on the
+	 heap boundary.  This was not a problem before glibc 2.26 because
+	 fastbin consolidation created large enough regions for the trim
+	 path to work.  tcache broke that by intercepting free() before
+	 consolidation.  */
+      size_t ps = GLRO (dl_pagesize);
+      char *paligned = PTR_ALIGN_UP ((char *) p
+				     + sizeof (struct malloc_chunk), ps);
+      char *pend = PTR_ALIGN_DOWN ((char *) p + size, ps);
+      if (pend > paligned)
+	__madvise (paligned, pend - paligned, MADV_DONTNEED);
+
       if (av == &main_arena)
 	{
 #ifndef MORECORE_CANNOT_TRIM
@@ -4355,7 +4371,7 @@ _int_free_merge_chunk (...)

   /* Write the chunk header, maybe after merging with the following chunk.  */
   size = _int_free_create_chunk (av, p, size, nextchunk, nextsize);
-  _int_free_maybe_trim (av, size);
+  _int_free_maybe_trim (av, p, size);
 }
